**naming variable rules**

1. all identifiers will begin with letter, dollar sign, underscore

2. the variablea can contain numbers or letters dollar signs or underscores but no special characters you can't use between space

3. you can't name a data type like let let a = 13

4. variable name are case sensitive

5. Naming Conventions ***camelCase***

e g.

let firstName = "Rye";

let lastName = "Ryan";
let y = true;

console.log(typeof y);

let z = "Rye Ryan";

console.log(typeof z);

